.START 

Cie. de Saint Gobain said consolidated net income after payments to minority interests rose 15% to 2.01 billion French francs ($305.7 million) in the first half of 1989, reflecting continued strong demand across most major markets and product ranges. 

The Paris glass and building materials group had net income of 1.75 billion francs a year ago.
Consolidated revenue gained 12% to 33.2 billion francs from 29.6 billion francs. 

Operating profit gained 17% to 4.75 billion francs from 4.06 billion francs.
The company said one-time gains from asset sales eased to 95 million francs from 443 million francs. 

Saint Gobain's finances generally improved.
While restructuring provisions rose 12% to 606 million francs, net financial costs declined 8% to 672 million francs and non-operating charges fell 29% to 284 million francs. 

These elements helped generate consolidated cash flow of 3.96 billion francs, up 17%, well above investments, which rose 36% to 2.83 billion francs. 

